## Engineering Manager
>At Teko, with nearly 200 talented engineers in many fields, we work and share knowledge in the application of advanced technology platforms such as Cloud, Big Data, Al, … In addition, Teko Ventures is investing strongly in the fields of Fintech, New Retail, Logistics, Warehouse, Digital Entertainment, B2B Management Solutio
### Your responsibilities:
- Work closely with product managers to ensure we’re building the best products and deliver the most value to customers.
- Manage a team of software engineers, including task planning, design and code review.
- Facilitate development process, work to remove all impediments and obstructions to the team’s progress.
- Be responsible for the overall planning, execution and success of complex technical projects.
- Drive technical projects, innovation, leadership, endeavors to build a safe environment and promote a productive culture for work.You will be part of an agile team, work with the SA to create a secure, scalable infrastructure for large-scale applications.
### Requirements:
- Degree/Masters in Computer Science, Software Engineering or other equivalent degrees/experience.
- Experience in two or more of the following programming languages: Python, Golang and Java.
- Experience in designing and implementing large-scale software products.
- Ability to facilitate the development process and use your experience to drive change and help engineers solve complex problems.
- Passionate about building high performance, self-sustaining teams with strong engineering culture and ability to coach and mentor team members in their professional development
### Our current tech stacks:
- Infrastructure: Linux, Network, Storage (Ceph), Kubernetes on bare metal.
- CI/CD: Ansible, Spinnaker, Docker.
- Application layers: Python, Golang, Java.
- Distributed systems: Elasticsearch, Apache Spark
- Databases: MongoDB, Redis, MySQL.
### Benefits:
- Negotiable salary according to qualification (13th month salary + KPI Bonus) ;
- The working environment is open, energetic and professional. More opportunities for career promotion;
- Free Food & Drink: Providing lunch, Fresh fruit/cake, Coffee,Tea & Beer.
- Full benefit with social insurance. Annual health check and Generali insurance under the company’s own policy;
- Employee Relationship: company trip, monthly team building;
- Leave Paid: 12 days for annual leave & 6 days for sick leave (max 18days)
